            "icon_alt_text": "Icon Description",
            "icon_title": "Grayanotoxin I (GTX I)",
            "icon_description": "Grayanotoxin I (GTX I) is a crucial neurotoxin in the leaves of Rhododen-dron flowers that acts as a shield for insect and vertebrate herbivores. Grayanotoxin I (GTX I) is present in the nectar of various Rhododendron species, with a phenotypic correlation between GTX I concentrations in leaves and nectar, showing high interspecific variation and significantly higher concentrations in leaves compared to nectar or petals.",
