            "icon_alt_text": "",
            "icon_title": "Grayanotoxin III (GTX III)",
            "icon_description": "Ten samples of a special type of honey called \"mad honey\" from Turkey we-re tested to measure the amount of a compound called GTX-III, which can cause poisoning. GTX-III works by blocking sodium channels in the cell membrane, which affects how cells function. The concentration of GTX-III in these honey samples ranged from very low (0.701 µg/g) to high (68.754 µg/g), with the highest amount found in a sample from Artvin/Hopa (MH7), an area already known for causing grayanotoxin poisoning.",
            "btn_title": "",
            "btn_link": ""
          }
        }
